plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 shows the results from simulations of varying sequence lengths, for longer
 sequences the percentage of errors converges to 25%, just as the model
 predicts.
 Also shown is the variance 
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
removed 'around'
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in the percentage of errors around 
\begin_inset Formula $x=50$
\end_inset

.
 Assuming the distance from 
\begin_inset Formula $25\%$
\end_inset

 in each direction is three standard deviations away, the percentage around
 
\begin_inset Formula $x=50$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $0.25_{-0.0449}^{+0.0577}$
\end_inset

 (1
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 in each direction) which makes our measurement 
\begin_inset Formula $1.8$
\end_inset

 standard deviations away, well within the desired range.
